# 61_actions_view_toggle_smoke — Tier 2 m11 View-toggle bool sweep (s256).
# Validates the two wrap-now stateful-bool verbs migrated from raw
# `Gio::SimpleAction::create_bool + activate handler` to
# `add_scripted_bool_action`:
#   - toggle-rulers
#   - toggle-outline
#
# **First PASS-observable smoke in Tier 2.** Smokes 52-60 all landed
# 0 PASS by design — the m1 first-batch and m3-m10 sweeps had no
# scriptable observables (canvas state isn't directly queryable from
# the wrapper). The stateful-bool helper opens a `<verb>_state` query
# per the audit fork 10 default (carry-forward 2 in the s255→s256
# handoff ratified YES on the readback question). This smoke uses
# the readback to assert flip semantics via the 4-phase shape
# (read-initial / flip / read-flipped / flip-back) named in the
# handoff.
#
# ── What this smoke exercises ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Eleven observables: 1 list + 8 trace lines (4 asserts + 4 invokes
# across the two verbs) + 2 refusals.
#
# Per verb, the 4-phase shape:
#   1. assert initial state (PASS)
#   2. flip via parameterless invoke (trace `ok`)
#   3. assert flipped state (PASS)
#   4. flip back via parameterless invoke (trace `ok`)
#
# Total PASS observables: 4 (two per verb × two verbs).
#
# ── Caller / mask ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ScripterWindow listener, RunContext::Scripter. Both verbs declare
# Scripter | TestRunner per wrap-now default. Macro is OUT — view
# toggles are user-preference-level, not part of a recordable macro
# story; matches the m1 first-batch posture.
#
# ── Test isolation ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Each verb's 4-phase ends with the state flipped back to its initial
# value — the smoke is idempotent. Side effects during the smoke:
#
#   - `win toggle-rulers` — phase 2 hides rulers, phase 4 shows them
#     again (assuming initial=visible). Visual channel: rulers and
#     corner widget flicker off then back on across the smoke.
#   - `win toggle-outline` — phase 2 switches preview→outline mode,
#     phase 4 switches outline→preview. Visual channel: canvas
#     rendering style flips for one beat.
#
# **Outline-mode caveat.** The setter refuses outline→preview at
# unsafe zoom (drop-shadow Cairo buffer threshold; see Canvas.hpp
# preview_safe_at_current_zoom). If Scott runs this smoke at extreme
# zoom (>~50× on a 1000² doc), phase 4 will alert + refuse, and
# the assertion in phase 5 (state should be back to initial false)
# will FAIL because the canvas is still in outline mode. Run from
# a normal zoom level — the precondition is "ordinary view," same
# baseline as smokes 52-60.
#
# ── Precondition reminders ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Curvz running with project + doc open.
# 2. Rulers VISIBLE (default state) — smoke assumes initial
#    `toggle-rulers_state == true`. If rulers are hidden at smoke
#    start, the first assert fails and the rest of the smoke produces
#    misleading reads. Check View → Rulers before running; if hidden,
#    show them.
# 3. Outline mode OFF (default state) — smoke assumes initial
#    `toggle-outline_state == false`. Same fix if it's on: View →
#    Outline Mode to turn off before the smoke.
# 4. Zoom at a normal level (not >~50×) so the outline→preview
#    transition in phase 8 doesn't trigger the safety refusal.

#[sub] === Phase 1: registry sanity-check — `win` is still registered ===

#[sub] `list` enumerates every registered Scriptable. The output should
#[sub] include a `win` line, same as smokes 52-60. The new `toggle-
#[sub] rulers_state` and `toggle-outline_state` properties don't appear
#[sub] in `list` output (which is Scriptables, not properties), but
#[sub] they're queryable via `query` per phases 2 / 4 / 6 / 8.

list

#[sub] === Phase 2: toggle-rulers initial-state read (PASS) ===

#[sub] First PASS observable in Tier 2. The `<verb>_state` property
#[sub] resolves via ActionGroupScriptable::query() — it strips the
#[sub] `_state` suffix, looks the verb up in m_actions, and returns
#[sub] ScriptValue::boolean of the action's current state IF the
#[sub] entry is StatefulBool. Stateless entries return null and the
#[sub] assert fails with a kind-mismatch (not an `error invoke threw`
#[sub] but a proper PASS/FAIL slot — first one for this Scriptable).

assert win toggle-rulers_state == true

#[sub] === Phase 3: toggle-rulers flip via parameterless activate ===

#[sub] Zero-arg invocation routes through ActionGroupScriptable::invoke's
#[sub] StatefulBool branch → entry.action->activate() → helper's
#[sub] activate lambda reads current=true, calls setter(false) → setter
#[sub] hides rulers, set_state(false). Trace channel: `ok`.

win toggle-rulers

#[sub] === Phase 4: toggle-rulers flipped-state read (PASS) ===

#[sub] State should now be false. Confirms the flip semantics work
#[sub] end-to-end: activate → helper lambda → setter → set_state →
#[sub] query reads back.

assert win toggle-rulers_state == false

#[sub] === Phase 5: toggle-rulers flip back to leave state idempotent ===

#[sub] Final flip restores the initial state. Smoke is replay-safe.

win toggle-rulers

#[sub] === Phase 6: toggle-outline initial-state read (PASS) ===

#[sub] Symmetric to phase 2 for the outline verb. Initial state
#[sub] expected: false (preview mode is the default).

assert win toggle-outline_state == false

#[sub] === Phase 7: toggle-outline flip — preview→outline ===

#[sub] Always-safe direction (outline mode is safe at any zoom).
#[sub] Setter: is_outline_mode==false, v==true → flips, signal fires,
#[sub] sync wire calls set_state(true).

win toggle-outline

#[sub] === Phase 8: toggle-outline flipped-state read (PASS) ===

#[sub] State should now be true. Same end-to-end confirmation as
#[sub] phase 4 but via the signal-driven sync path (the outline setter
#[sub] doesn't call set_state itself; the canvas signal does).

assert win toggle-outline_state == true

#[sub] === Phase 9: toggle-outline flip back — outline→preview ===

#[sub] Safety-gated direction. At normal zoom this is fine; if Scott's
#[sub] zoom is over the threshold, the setter refuses (alert, return
#[sub] early) and the action state stays at true. See precondition #4.

win toggle-outline

#[sub] === Phase 10: unknown-verb refusal ===

#[sub] Same shape as every Tier 2 smoke's refusal phase. `win quit` is
#[sub] bucket-C (future app.quit) and not in the wrapper's verb surface.

win quit

#[sub] === Phase 11: wrong-shape argument refusal ===

#[sub] Stateful bool invoke accepts 0 args (toggle) or 1 Bool arg (set
#[sub] explicitly). A string argument is neither shape; the StatefulBool
#[sub] invoke branch refuses with "takes 0 args (toggle) or 1 bool arg
#[sub] (set explicitly)."

win toggle-rulers "not a bool"

#[sub] === Predicted observables ───────────────────────────────────────────

#[sub] Expected summary line:
#[sub]
#[sub]   11 lines, 4 pass, 0 fail, 2 error
#[sub]
#[sub] - 4 PASS  : phases 2, 4, 6, 8 — the 4-phase shape across two
#[sub]             stateful-bool verbs. **First non-zero PASS count in
#[sub]             any Tier 2 smoke.**
#[sub] - 0 fail  : all asserts predict TRUE for initial / FALSE after
#[sub]             flip / FALSE for initial / TRUE after flip.
#[sub] - 2 error : phases 10 and 11 — unknown verb, wrong-shape arg.
#[sub] - 1 operator-visual list block (phase 1).
#[sub] - 4 operator-visual `ok` echoes from the four invokes (phases
#[sub]             3, 5, 7, 9).
#[sub] - 2 operator-visual refusal lines (phases 10, 11).
#[sub]
#[sub] **What the prediction depends on:**
#[sub]
#[sub] - Preconditions met (rulers visible, outline off, normal zoom).
#[sub] - The helper's activate lambda correctly reads current state
#[sub]   and inverts (phase 3 + phase 5).
#[sub] - The setter for rulers writes m_rulers_visible AND calls
#[sub]   set_state (no signal-driven sync exists for rulers).
#[sub] - The setter for outline DOESN'T call set_state — the canvas
#[sub]   signal does (signal_outline_mode_changed in
#[sub]   MainWindow_bindings.cpp:1449).
#[sub] - The query layer correctly handles the `<verb>_state` suffix
#[sub]   (suffix-strip and StatefulBool kind-check before reading
#[sub]   action state).
#[sub]
#[sub] Tier 2 row ticks 5/49 → 46/48 = 95.8% with this smoke and the
#[sub] s256 m1 audit correction (denominator drops 49 → 48). **First
#[sub] non-zero PASS reading on the Tier 2 row.** Remaining 2 open
#[sub] are fork-3 (translate-dialog) awaiting Scott's A-vs-B
#[sub] ratification.
